  <span id="freeText17471358921964371257" style="display:none">Oh to be a doctor in rural apparently was not a good thing because the people would not listen when you tried to tell them about STDs, in particular, syphilis<br />	Oh, to be a patient in rural Russia where doctors come after graduating and having no experience.<br />	This is the basis for the Ovation/BBC series of the same name, and a reader can see why it had so many champions for adaption. IT is at time poignant and at times very funny. It feels very true. It should be noted that if you have seen the series, this book contains several of the cases that are used in the first season. It also lacks the magical realism flair of the series (though Bulgakov himself would use magic realism). <br /></span>
